- `const SEED_FLAG = 'flowguard_incidents_seeded'`

**Replace the mount `useEffect` (current `seedAndFetch` block):**
```js
// Before (lines 289–313): wraps fetchIncidents inside seedAndFetch
// After:
useEffect(() => {
  fetchIncidents();
}, [fetchIncidents]);
```

**Add `silent` flag to `fetchIncidents`** so background polling doesn't trigger the loading bar:
```js
const fetchIncidents = useCallback(async (silent = false) => {
  if (!silent) setLoading(true);
  try {
    const res = await axios.get('/api/incident', {
      headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${getToken()}` },
    });
    setIncidents(Array.isArray(res.data) ? res.data : []);
  } catch (err) {
    console.error('Failed to fetch incidents:', err);
    if (!silent) showToast('Failed to load incidents from server.', 'error');
  } finally {
    if (!silent) setLoading(false);
  }
}, [showToast]);
```

---

## Step 3 — Multi-Row Animation: `newRowId` → `newRowIds`

**State declaration:**
```js
// Remove:
const [newRowId, setNewRowId] = useState(null);
// Add:
const [newRowIds, setNewRowIds] = useState(new Set());
```

**`handleCreate` update** (the single-row create action):
```js
// Remove:
setNewRowId(res.data.id);
setTimeout(() => setNewRowId(null), 700);
// Add:
setNewRowIds(prev => new Set([...prev, res.data.id]));
setTimeout(() => {
  setNewRowIds(prev => { const n = new Set(prev); n.delete(res.data.id); return n; });
}, 700);
```

**Row class update** (in the table map):
```js
const rowClass = [
  newRowIds.has(incident.id)       ? 'inc-row-new'      : '',
  incident.id === deletingId       ? 'inc-row-deleting'  : '',
  incident.source === 'Manual'     ? 'inc-row-manual'    : '',
].filter(Boolean).join(' ');
```

---

## Step 4 — Background Polling

**Add `pollForNewIncidents` callback** (after `fetchIncidents`):
```js
const pollForNewIncidents = useCallback(async () => {
  try {
    const res = await axios.get('/api/incident', {
      headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${getToken()}` },
    });
    const freshData = Array.isArray(res.data) ? res.data : [];

    setIncidents(prev => {
      const existingIds = new Set(prev.map(i => i.id));
      const brandNew = freshData.filter(i => !existingIds.has(i.id));

      if (brandNew.length === 0) return prev; // no change, skip re-render

      const newIdSet = new Set(brandNew.map(i => i.id));
      setNewRowIds(cur => new Set([...cur, ...newIdSet]));
      setTimeout(() => {
        setNewRowIds(cur => {
          const n = new Set(cur);
          newIdSet.forEach(id => n.delete(id));
          return n;
        });
      }, 700);

      return freshData;
    });
  } catch {
    // silent — polling errors not surfaced to user
  }
}, []); // empty deps: uses functional updater to avoid stale closures
```

**Why stale closures are avoided:** The `setIncidents(prev => ...)` functional form receives the current committed state as `prev` at execution time, regardless of when the closure was captured. The poll never reads `incidents` from its scope — it reads `prev` inside the updater.

**Add polling `useEffect`** (after the mount effect):
```js
useEffect(() => {
  const id = setInterval(pollForNewIncidents, 10_000);
  return () => clearInterval(id);
}, [pollForNewIncidents]);
```

---

## Step 5 — AI vs Manual Source Counter

**Add `sourceCounts` memo** (with the other `useMemo` blocks):
```js
const sourceCounts = useMemo(() => ({
  ai:     incidents.filter(i => i.source !== 'Manual').length,
  manual: incidents.filter(i => i.source === 'Manual').length,
}), [incidents]);
```

Uses `incidents` (full list), not `filtered` — counts should reflect total system state regardless of active filters.

**Add JSX** between the closing `</div>` of `inc-stats-grid` and the loading bar:
