=============================================================
FLOWGUARD — SESSION HANDOFF SUMMARY
Branch: feature/incident-tracking
Date: 28 June 2026
=============================================================

This session implemented live AI data seeding into the incident
dashboard, removing all placeholder data, and added a source
breakdown counter. No other pages or components were touched.

=============================================================
CHANGES MADE THIS SESSION
=============================================================

--- CHANGE 1: Server bridge — DetectionAlert → IncidentLog ---
File: server/routes/detectionAlerts.js

CONTEXT: The AI service's background YOLO detection loop fires
unattended-object alerts to POST /api/detection-alerts. Previously
this only saved to the DetectionAlert model and never appeared in
the incident dashboard.

FIX: After the DetectionAlert is saved and the 201 is returned to
the AI service, a fire-and-forget IncidentLog.create() runs. The
AI never waits for it — it always receives its 201 regardless of
whether the bridge succeeds.

Added at top of file:
  const { DetectionAlert, IncidentLog } = require('../models');

Added severity helper (before router definition):
  function severityFromDuration(seconds) {
    if (!seconds || seconds < 120) return 'Low';
    if (seconds < 300) return 'Medium';
    if (seconds < 600) return 'High';
    return 'Critical';
  }

Added inside router.post('/'), immediately after res.status(201).json(alert):
  IncidentLog.create({
    camera_location: camera_location,
    status: 'UNATTENDED_OBJECT',
    source: 'Object Detection',
    severity: severityFromDuration(duration_seconds),
    person_name: (person_name && person_name !== 'UNKNOWN') ? person_name : null,
    confidence_score: null,
    resolutionStatus: 'Active',
    notes: zone_name ? `[Object Detection] Zone: ${zone_name}` : ''
  }).catch(err =>
    console.error(`[Bridge] DetectionAlert id=${alert.id} — IncidentLog create failed:`, err.message)
  );

Field mapping table:
  camera_location     → camera_location   (direct)
  (hardcoded)         → status            UNATTENDED_OBJECT always
                                          (AI only fires _fire_alert on
                                          unattended objects)
  (hardcoded)         → source            'Object Detection'
  duration_seconds    → severity          via severityFromDuration()
  person_name         → person_name       null if missing or 'UNKNOWN'
  (none)              → confidence_score  always null
  (hardcoded)         → resolutionStatus  'Active'
  zone_name           → notes             '[Object Detection] Zone: {zone_name}'

--- CHANGE 2: Static seed removal ---
File: client/src/pages/IncidentDashboard.jsx

Removed entirely:
  - const T = (hoursAgo) => ... (timestamp helper)
  - const STATIC_INCIDENTS = [...] (12-item hardcoded array, 127 lines)
  - const SEED_FLAG = 'flowguard_incidents_seeded'

The seedAndFetch() async function (which looped over STATIC_INCIDENTS
posting each to the API, then set the localStorage flag) was replaced
with a single direct call:

  BEFORE:
    useEffect(() => {
      const seedAndFetch = async () => {
        if (!localStorage.getItem(SEED_FLAG)) { ... }
        await fetchIncidents();
      };
      seedAndFetch();
    }, [fetchIncidents]);

  AFTER:
    useEffect(() => {
      fetchIncidents();
    }, [fetchIncidents]);

NOTE: Any incidents already seeded into the DB from previous sessions
remain in the database. They can be deleted manually via the dashboard's
existing Delete button. The seeding mechanism will never run again.
The localStorage key 'flowguard_incidents_seeded' may still be present
in some browsers but is now inert.

--- CHANGE 3: fetchIncidents silent flag ---
File: client/src/pages/IncidentDashboard.jsx

Added a silent = false parameter to fetchIncidents so the background
polling can call it without triggering the loading bar or error toasts:

  BEFORE: const fetchIncidents = useCallback(async () => {
            setLoading(true);
            ...
            showToast('Failed to load...', 'error');
            ...
            setLoading(false);
          }, [showToast]);

  AFTER:  const fetchIncidents = useCallback(async (silent = false) => {
            if (!silent) setLoading(true);
            ...
            if (!silent) showToast('Failed to load...', 'error');
            ...
            if (!silent) setLoading(false);
          }, [showToast]);

--- CHANGE 4: newRowId → newRowIds (Set) ---
File: client/src/pages/IncidentDashboard.jsx

The previous single-value newRowId (null) was insufficient for live
polling — multiple new incidents could arrive in the same poll cycle.

  BEFORE: const [newRowId, setNewRowId] = useState(null);
